            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(a)",
          "text": "Shall not be less than 15% of the lot area and may include preserving existing woodlands or vegetation on site; 7.5 m Chain Link Fence 7.5 m, 20 m if bordering residential Min. Side Yard Setback 3 m; 6 m if bordering residential Must be buffered with landscaping when fronting directly on a street",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(b)",
          "text": "May permit the use of planting beds, grassy berms, bio-swales, and stormwater features as part of the landscape calculation;",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(c)",
          "text": "Requires native trees with a minimum height of 2.5 m at a rate of no less than 2 trees per acre.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(d)",
          "text": "Requires landscaped beds consisting of ornamental grasses, woody shrubs or perennials at a rate of no less than 0.5 m2 per metre of frontage of the principal building and located in the front yard.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": ".3",
          "text": "Properties that abut residential uses shall include a 3 m wide landscape buffer along the abutting property line that includes:",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(a)",
          "text": "A 1.8 m high (min.) opaque fence",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(b)",
          "text": "One 60 mm caliper tree per 8 m of side or rear yard planted in the landscape buffer placed to block light and views.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(c)",
          "text": "For buildings that have been set back more than 3 m from the front lot line, no less than 1 tree shall be planted per front yard.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": ".4",
          "text": "Any chain link fences fronting directly on a street must be buffered using a combination of trees, shrubs or vines.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": ".5",
          "text": "All disturbed areas should be well landscaped using mostly (>75% quantities) indigenous, low maintenance plants that are well adapted for the local microclimates on each site. Shade tolerant species shall be specified for the north side of buildings or in areas of frequent shade. Similarly, windy sites should be planted with wind tolerant species. Disturbed areas cannot be left without landscaping.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": ".6",
          "text": "Where grass is being considered for any project:",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(a)",
          "text": "Ensure the grass species is selected is adequate for shade levels on the site.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(b)",
          "text": "Pegged sod is required on all landscaped slopes exceeding 30%. Erosion Control measures must be clearly identified on sloping sites to minimize soil erosion.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(c)",
          "text": "A minimum of 1.5 m wide of Sod strip is required adjoining any asphalt areas, pathways, gravel storage areas, or landscape beds.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(d)",
          "text": "A minimum of 2 m wide strip of sod is required for all drainage swales",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(e)",
          "text": "Any reinstatement of public road right- of-ways must be sodded.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": "(f)",
          "text": "Hydraulic seeding is permitted in all other areas where sod is not required. Broadcast seed is not permitted unless used for spot repairs.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": ".7",
          "text": "For any parking lots located in the front yard, a minimum 2 m wide hard surfaced sidewalk shall connect the front door of the building to any adjacent sidewalks adjoining the property if present.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": ".8",
          "text": "Slopes shall be no steeper that three (3) horizontal to one (1) vertical, except as an engineered retaining structure. All slopes shall be vegetated (not necessarily grass) and no riprap stone armouring is permitted on any site unless it is not materially visible from any road or sidewalk.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": ".9",
          "text": "All main entries should be well landscaped to a scale that is appropriate for the scale of the building and the importance of the entry sequence.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": ".10",
          "text": "The front door of the primary building must connect to adjacent sidewalks and parking areas by a hard surfaced walkway no less than 1.8 m wide.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": ".11",
          "text": "Parking is recommended in the side or rear yard of the lot, but any parking located in front yard of the primary building shall include one additional tree for every 10 parking spaces located in the front yard.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        },
        {
          "provision_label_raw": ".12",
          "text": "The development officer may forgo these landscape requirements if it can be demonstrated that any of these requirements do not apply on a specific site. In addition, they may require additional requirements on a site specific basis to deal with special site consequences.",
          "status": "active",
          "citations": {
            "pdf_page_start": 136,
            "pdf_page_end": 136,
            "bylaw_page_start": 132,
            "bylaw_page_end": 132
          }
        }
